{"type":"message","id":"5d10fa75","parentId":"7d1b4d8e","timestamp":"2026-03-23T00:26:58.561Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I notice all VRs are 1.0 which seems suspicious. Let me check if the volume ratio calculation is correct. Also, the晋级概率 seems very low across the board, all below 15%. Let me verify the VR calculation and also check the market sentiment.\n\nActually wait, looking at the results, all stocks have VR=1.0 which is suspicious - it seems like the VR calculation might be wrong. Let me check the kline.py vol_ma function.\n\nAlso, the晋级概率 for almost all stocks is below 15%, which means there are no stocks in the >30% or 15-30% range. This would result in empty sections in the report.\n\n\nLooking at the phase adjustment in predict.py, it applies a 0.40× discount for the '退潮' phase, which is likely contributing to these low probability scores. The VR calculation might be the core issue though - the vol_ma function returns the 20-day moving average of volume, but the ratio calculation in get_kline isn't properly dividing by the recent volume average to get the actual ratio.\n\nI'm also noticing that many stocks show RSI values above 90, which suggests they're heavily overbought. I should adjust the market phase from '退潮' to '启动' or '发酵' to see if that improves the probability estimates, and I need to verify how the BaoStock data is being returned to understand why the VR calculations are coming out as 1.0.","thinkingSignature":"a79bea76311f4645035aa16d05c32e6de353b4d0d14012727a33e1f48410c459"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_isgqa5czhkjq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace && python3 << 'EOF'\nimport sys\nsys.path.insert(0, '.')\nfrom astock.kline import get_kline\nimport baostock as bs\nbs.login()\n\n# Debug: check VR for a few stocks\nfor code in ['000020', '000601', '603687']:\n    kl = get_kline(code, days=60)\n    if kl:\n        print(f\"\\n{code}:\")\n        print(f\"  vr = {kl.get('vr')}\")\n        print(f\"  vol_status = {kl.get('vol_status')}\")\n        print(f\"  last 5 vols = {kl['vols'][-5:]}\")\n        print(f\"  ma20_vol = volume MA20\")\n        # Calculate manually\n        vols = kl['vols']\n        vol_ma20 = sum(vols[-20:]) / 20\n        recent_vol = vols[-1]\n        print(f\"  sum last 20 vols = {sum(vols[-20:])}\")\n        print(f\"  ma20 = {vol_ma20:.2f}\")\n        print(f\"  recent_vol = {recent_vol:.2f}\")\n        print(f\"  vr_manual = {vol_ma20/recent_vol:.2f}\" if recent_vol else \"N/A\")\n        \nbs.logout()\nEOF","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":13315,"output":621,"cacheRead":27169,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41105,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774225606434}}
