{"type":"message","id":"66ec964d","parentId":"3e60c653","timestamp":"2026-03-23T00:27:16.037Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's clearly a bug in the VR calculation in get_kline. The formula is:\n```python\nrecent_vol_avg = sum(vols[-20:]) / 20\nvr = vol_ma20 / recent_vol_avg if recent_vol_avg else None\n```\n\nWait, that doesn't match. `vol_ma20` is the 20-day MA of volume, and `recent_vol_avg` is also the 20-day average. So `vr = vol_ma20 / recent_vol_avg` would always be approximately 1.0! That's the bug.\n\nLooking at the kline.py code:\n```python\n\n\nvol_ma20 = vol_ma(vols, 20)\n...\nvr = vol_ma20 / recent_vol_avg if recent_vol_avg else None\n```\n\nBut `vol_ma20` and `recent_vol_avg` are the same calculation, so they're always nearly identical, making the ratio always ~1.0. The correct formula should compare today's volume to the 20-day average, not divide the 20-day MA by itself.\n\nI can work around this by calculating the volume ratio directly in my screening script using the correct formula: recent volume divided by the 20-day average. This is the standard 量比 definition used in Chinese stock analysis. I'll also need to adjust the market phase from '退潮' to something more appropriate based on the 28 limit-up stocks I observed.\n\nLooking at the sector breakdown, I can see the market has a strong sector rotation pattern with electricity stocks dominating at 7, followed by photovoltaic equipment at 5, while most other sectors have just 1-2 stocks. The 28 limit-up stocks suggest moderate market enthusiasm. Since this is a Monday after a weekend gap, the previous trading day was Friday, so I need to pull the market sentiment data from that session to get a clearer picture of the actual market state.","thinkingSignature":"c92385bd50038a3e5deddef922ea27904844c5fb9c50d94129bff91a269dde3b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1spfy64kynhr_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace && python3 << 'EOF'\nimport sys\nsys.path.insert(0, '.')\nimport akshare as ak\nimport baostock as bs\n\nbs.login()\n\n# Get market sentiment data for previous trading day\ntry:\n    zt_pool_df = ak.stock_zt_pool_em(date='20260320')\n    zt_count = len(zt_pool_df)\n    # 炸板率 = 炸板次数 / (涨停+炸板)\n    zha_ban = zt_pool_df['炸板次数'].sum()\n    zt_with_zb = zt_pool_df[zt_pool_df['炸板次数'] > 0]\n    zha_ban_rate = zha_ban / zt_count * 100 if zt_count > 0 else 0\n    print(f\"涨停股数量: {zt_count}\")\n    print(f\"炸板次数: {zha_ban}\")\n    print(f\"炸板率: {zha_ban_rate:.1f}%\")\n    \n    # Average turnover for 1st board stocks\n    lb1 = zt_pool_df[zt_pool_df['连板数'] == 1]\n    print(f\"首板股数量: {len(lb1)}, 平均换手率: {lb1['换手率'].mean():.1f}%\")\n    \n    # Sector with most zt stocks\n    sector_zt = zt_pool_df.groupby('所属行业').size().sort_values(ascending=False)\n    print(f\"\\n涨停板块分布:\\n{sector_zt}\")\n    \nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"Error: {e}\")\n\nbs.logout()\nEOF","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":14303,"output":772,"cacheRead":27169,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42244,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774225622427}}
